# Q2 Threat Outlook (clean)

## Executive summary

We assess with moderate confidence that Volt Typhoon will likely continue prepositioning in U.S. critical-infrastructure networks through Q3, based on the CISA / NSA / FBI joint advisory from March and corroborating telemetry shared via the MS-ISAC in April.

## Analysis

Volt Typhoon activity, attributed by the CISA / NSA / FBI joint advisory and a Microsoft Threat Intelligence report from February, focused on LOTL techniques (T1059.001, T1078.002) against network-edge devices.

Per the CISA advisory, "the actor maintains long-term persistence through valid accounts and built-in tools." That phrasing matches our own observations from one regional GC's telemetry in Q1 (low confidence on the broader pattern).

We assess with high confidence, based on three independent sources (Microsoft, CISA, and Mandiant), that exploitation of CVE-2026-0001 will very likely accelerate over the next 60 days.

## Recommendations

Prioritize EDR coverage for edge devices. Patch CVE-2026-0001 on internet-facing systems first. Re-baseline service accounts in subsidiaries that have not enforced phishing-resistant MFA.
